Package com.irurueta.navigation.inertial

Class ECIKinematics

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.ECIorECEFKinematics<ECIKinematics>
      • com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.ECIKinematics
  • public class ECIKinematics
extends ECIorECEFKinematics<ECIKinematics>
    Describes the motion of a body based on the specific forces (i.e. specific accelerations) and angular rates applied to it with respect the ECI frame and resolved along body-frame axes. Body frame axes are typically defined so that x is the forward axis, pointing in the usual direction of travel, z is the down axis, pointing in the usual direction of gravity, and y is the right axis, completing the orthogonal set.
